00:02:12.080 --> 00:02:18.070
All right, so let's talk about
why it's so essential to make sure

00:02:18.070 --> 00:02:22.080
that your menu,
your navigation menu is accessible.

00:02:22.080 --> 00:02:27.370
So on this slide,
I have a picture of a person sitting

00:02:27.370 --> 00:02:35.110
in a rowboat looking tranquilly over
this peaceful scene of this lake

00:02:35.110 --> 00:02:36.740
that he is floating on.

00:02:36.740 --> 00:02:41.040
There is however one thing
notably missing from this picture

00:02:41.040 --> 00:02:43.290
and that is any oars.

00:02:43.290 --> 00:02:51.040
So this person has no way of
actually moving around this locale.

00:02:52.670 --> 00:02:59.600
So it’s going to be problematic
for the person coming in.

00:02:59.600 --> 00:03:07.600
If we say that your site is akin
to this scene, your menu is going

00:03:09.100 --> 00:03:12.970
to be those paddles, it's going to
be the way that your visitors have

00:03:12.970 --> 00:03:18.640
of moving around your site
in the way that they need to.

00:03:18.640 --> 00:03:21.450
And so without a paddle,
you are in trouble.

00:03:22.760 --> 00:03:26.540
Getting around is hard without a
good navigation menu that works

00:03:26.540 --> 00:03:28.130
for everybody.

00:03:28.130 --> 00:03:34.260
So often, people put a lot of
thought and effort into making sure

00:03:34.260 --> 00:03:38.600
that their navigation
menu works pretty well,

00:03:40.900 --> 00:03:42.970
and that it does the things
that they want it to.

00:03:42.970 --> 00:03:47.820
But if it's not accessible,
then a whole segment

00:03:47.820 --> 00:03:50.060
of their audience is not
able to use it in the way

00:03:50.060 --> 00:03:50.990
that they are intending.

00:03:50.990 --> 00:03:55.920
And so we have got to make
sure that they can do that.

00:03:55.920 --> 00:04:01.640
Now, internal page links can
work if you disregard the ability

00:04:01.640 --> 00:04:02.640
to use the menu.

00:04:03.750 --> 00:04:05.740
So you can direct
people around your site

00:04:05.740 --> 00:04:07.450
through just internal page links.

00:04:07.450 --> 00:04:08.510
That's an OK thing.

00:04:08.510 --> 00:04:10.650
The further navigation is
almost always accessible

00:04:10.650 --> 00:04:14.490
because there are no dropdowns or
complications as far as that goes.

00:04:16.340 --> 00:04:19.670
And many people are coming from
Google anyhow, so they will come

00:04:19.670 --> 00:04:24.895
to the precise page that
Google thinks they want,

00:04:24.896 --> 00:04:27.090
which often is true.

00:04:27.090 --> 00:04:35.090
However, in the final analysis, you
do want people to stay on your site,

00:04:36.630 --> 00:04:39.010
and in the end,
it is a numbers game.

00:04:39.010 --> 00:04:40.690
What do I mean by that?

00:04:40.690 --> 00:04:44.600
I mean that with your
visitors on your site, you are

00:04:44.600 --> 00:04:47.950
in a race against time.

00:04:47.950 --> 00:04:50.090
So here's some numbers to look at.

00:04:50.090 --> 00:04:52.770
54, what is that?

00:04:52.770 --> 00:04:58.760
Well, 54 actually is the average
number of seconds spent on a page.

00:04:58.760 --> 00:05:06.760
So less than a minute,
internet-wide, the length of time

00:05:07.470 --> 00:05:13.010
that people are actually gonna
be absorbing a page worth

00:05:13.010 --> 00:05:17.250
of information before they are
looking to go to their next page.

00:05:18.880 --> 00:05:20.750
Next number, five to seven.

00:05:20.750 --> 00:05:21.590
Well, what's that?

00:05:21.590 --> 00:05:25.150
That's the average number of
pages visited per session.

00:05:25.150 --> 00:05:28.610
So they will come onto your site
and they will stay on your site

00:05:28.610 --> 00:05:33.840
for an average number of five to
seven distinct pages of your site.

00:05:34.880 --> 00:05:39.460
Well, so you hope that you can
get them to the right place

00:05:39.460 --> 00:05:41.770
within those five to seven pages.

00:05:43.950 --> 00:05:48.070
Let's look at the average depth of
your best converting call to action.

00:05:48.070 --> 00:05:52.300
So on one of your pages,
it's what you want them to get to.

00:05:52.300 --> 00:05:56.080
How many pages do they have
to go through to get there?

00:05:56.080 --> 00:05:58.180
And I don't know
the answer to that.

00:05:58.180 --> 00:05:59.940
Probably nobody knows
the answer to that.

00:05:59.940 --> 00:06:03.420
It would be a very difficult
number to figure out.

00:06:03.420 --> 00:06:07.640
But what is certain is it's almost
certainly not the first page

00:06:07.640 --> 00:06:08.490
that they land on.

00:06:08.490 --> 00:06:13.740
So you are going to want to
provide people with a good way

00:06:13.740 --> 00:06:17.570
to get around your
site, hence the menu.

00:06:17.570 --> 00:06:22.950
But it needs to be accessible so
that all your visitors can use it.

00:06:22.950 --> 00:06:27.180
I've got my links to where
I got this information.

00:06:28.270 --> 00:06:33.130
And then my next slide says
menus may save bounces.

00:06:33.130 --> 00:06:37.050
One of the big benefits of having
a good menu, a well-designed menu,

00:06:37.050 --> 00:06:39.540
is that it will save bounces.

00:06:39.540 --> 00:06:42.080
So people won't come to your site,
not find what they are looking for,

00:06:42.080 --> 00:06:45.030
and jump off to another place.

00:06:45.030 --> 00:06:48.920
They will actually spend
some time on your site.

00:06:50.080 --> 00:06:50.800
Why?

00:06:50.800 --> 00:06:54.080
I say that your menu is
kind of like an old friend.

00:06:54.080 --> 00:07:01.200
Makes people feel
comfortable on your site.

00:07:01.200 --> 00:07:03.710
Makes them feel like they
know what's going on,

00:07:03.710 --> 00:07:05.420
and they can understand things.

00:07:06.570 --> 00:07:11.020
But this is only if they
can use your menu well.

00:07:12.120 --> 00:07:17.980
Your menu can be a springboard
into the other areas

00:07:17.980 --> 00:07:25.220
where they will actually find
the things that you are hoping

00:07:25.220 --> 00:07:28.030
that they will find.

00:07:29.270 --> 00:07:33.700
Your menu needs to avoid
some common problems.

00:07:33.700 --> 00:07:38.620
And I think a lot of people don't...
The menu was kind of given to them.

00:07:38.620 --> 00:07:41.760
It was part of the theme or
whatever that they're using

00:07:41.760 --> 00:07:43.470
to develop the site.

00:07:43.470 --> 00:07:45.920
And they do not
think a lot about it,

00:07:45.920 --> 00:07:49.380
but there are some common problems
that your menu needs to avoid.

00:07:50.670 --> 00:07:53.960
So what problems might be
lurking in your WordPress menu?

00:07:53.960 --> 00:08:00.230
On this screen, I have a
background image of a crocodile,

00:08:02.720 --> 00:08:10.160
just looking out half
concealed under the water.

00:08:10.160 --> 00:08:13.370
Oops, let's see.

00:08:13.370 --> 00:08:15.940
So what problems might be
lurking in your WordPress menu?

00:08:15.940 --> 00:08:17.100
OK, so problem number one.

00:08:19.450 --> 00:08:27.450
Your menu might only drop down
on hover and not focus or click.

00:08:30.310 --> 00:08:33.370
What this means is that if
you have a drop down menu...

00:08:35.220 --> 00:08:41.580
I have a couple of images here of
my favorite site for black history,

00:08:41.580 --> 00:08:45.130
which is blackpast.org,
which I've worked on.

00:08:45.130 --> 00:08:52.560
When I started working on it,
the menu dropped down on hover,

00:08:52.560 --> 00:08:53.850
but not on focus.

00:08:53.850 --> 00:08:58.750
So I have this image
of their website

00:08:58.750 --> 00:09:05.870
and someone hovering over the
African American history menu item

00:09:05.870 --> 00:09:09.630
and it drops down and we see
this drop down with a lot

00:09:11.130 --> 00:09:14.880
of secondary menu items in there.

00:09:14.880 --> 00:09:22.690
And then the second image I
have is showing the same menu,

00:09:22.690 --> 00:09:27.850
but now it has the focus indicator
on that primary menu item,

00:09:27.850 --> 00:09:30.870
but nothing is dropping down.

00:09:30.870 --> 00:09:33.270
With many websites,
this is what you get.

00:09:34.320 --> 00:09:39.990
You can see that you can tab
into the primary menu item,

00:09:39.990 --> 00:09:41.090
but it does not drop down.

00:09:41.090 --> 00:09:47.710
So you can't have access to all
of these secondary menu items

00:09:47.710 --> 00:09:50.530
that you've put in
there for a good reason.

00:09:50.530 --> 00:09:53.670
So a little closer look at this.

00:09:53.670 --> 00:09:57.300
Once again,
this is what it looks like on hover.

00:09:57.300 --> 00:10:01.740
So if you're hovering over this
category, all these drop downs.

00:10:01.740 --> 00:10:07.210
The second one, well,
I guess we missed the second one,

00:10:07.210 --> 00:10:08.480
it is just the same.

00:10:08.480 --> 00:10:11.180
It's just a closer look.

00:10:11.180 --> 00:10:15.530
OK, the next slide here goes
through why this is a problem.

00:10:15.530 --> 00:10:17.460
Well, who defects?

00:10:17.460 --> 00:10:22.650
If you are able to tab into
the primary menu items,

00:10:22.650 --> 00:10:26.600
but not the secondary menu items,
then this affects keyboard users

00:10:26.600 --> 00:10:29.640
because now all those
people who are navigating

00:10:30.840 --> 00:10:33.880
because they can not use mice,
maybe their mice are broken

00:10:33.880 --> 00:10:39.740
or they have got tremors and so they
can not have the fine motor control

00:10:39.740 --> 00:10:44.290
to actually use a mouse
to get around the site.

00:10:45.800 --> 00:10:47.900
Or people who just prefer
to navigate by keyboard.

00:10:47.900 --> 00:10:50.560
There are many reasons
why people might.

00:10:50.560 --> 00:10:57.170
And so there's a certain
portion of the population

00:10:57.170 --> 00:11:02.230
that will just navigate
your site by keyboard.

00:11:02.230 --> 00:11:07.590
And so having your menu only dropping
down on hover influences them

00:11:07.590 --> 00:11:10.110
or stops their ability
to use the menu.

00:11:11.220 --> 00:11:13.090
Also it could affect
switch device users.

00:11:13.090 --> 00:11:16.020
Those are users who
have a switch device

00:11:16.020 --> 00:11:19.410
where they only are using
one button to either advance

00:11:19.410 --> 00:11:24.580
or to select typically
that will move their focus,

00:11:26.020 --> 00:11:32.560
but it will not necessarily move
their cursor or their pointer.

00:11:32.560 --> 00:11:34.990
And so they would
not get the dropdown.

00:11:37.090 --> 00:11:40.890
Again, switch device users might
be people with no fine motor skills

00:11:40.890 --> 00:11:46.550
or limited people with cognitive
disabilities who it helps

00:11:46.550 --> 00:11:49.620
to just have an option of yay or
nay, yes or no.

00:11:51.600 --> 00:11:54.250
Sometimes this will also
affect screen reader users.

00:11:54.250 --> 00:11:57.710
Depending upon the
screen reader setup.

00:11:58.730 --> 00:12:04.720
So if it's set up for the virtual
cursor to follow the focus,

00:12:04.720 --> 00:12:11.990
then they might be fine
with your dropdown on hover.

00:12:11.990 --> 00:12:14.350
But if it's not set up that
way, then they

00:12:14.350 --> 00:12:17.763
might also have trouble using...

00:12:17.764 --> 00:12:22.350
We had an interesting
little interruption

00:12:25.710 --> 00:12:26.770
by a screen reader.

00:12:26.770 --> 00:12:29.120
But yes,
so that could be problematic.

00:12:31.510 --> 00:12:33.170
OK, our second problem here.

00:12:35.730 --> 00:12:43.390
If the dropdown works on
focus, but there's no ability

00:12:43.390 --> 00:12:46.050
to pull the menu back up.

00:12:46.050 --> 00:12:54.050
So what happens if this is the
case, is that when you tab

00:12:55.170 --> 00:13:00.510
into the menu and it drops
down, your next tab would be

00:13:00.510 --> 00:13:04.610
to the submenu item, and you
would have to go through that,

00:13:04.610 --> 00:13:07.770
which is OK if there are
only a few submenu items.

00:13:08.830 --> 00:13:13.720
With BlackPast, I have this
program that will enumerate

00:13:13.720 --> 00:13:15.800
how many tab stops are on the page.

00:13:15.800 --> 00:13:19.580
And as you can see,
to get to the bottom of this menu,

00:13:19.580 --> 00:13:23.860
you actually have 87 tab stops.

00:13:23.860 --> 00:13:29.230
So if you want to get to the
International Advisory Board

00:13:29.230 --> 00:13:35.280
in the About Us menu,
you would have to tab 87 times

00:13:35.280 --> 00:13:39.410
to get there, which is problematic.

00:13:39.410 --> 00:13:43.070
If you have the ability
to suck that menu back up,

00:13:43.070 --> 00:13:45.370
then you do not have that problem.

00:13:46.400 --> 00:13:47.780
All right, so who this affects?

00:13:47.780 --> 00:13:50.760
Once again, keyboard
users, switch device users,

00:13:50.760 --> 00:13:52.110
sometimes screen reader users.

00:13:53.810 --> 00:13:55.390
Why is it a problem?

00:13:55.390 --> 00:14:01.400
It probably exponentially
increases the amount of time needed

00:14:01.400 --> 00:14:03.290
to tab through the menu.

00:14:05.440 --> 00:14:09.920
So as I said, in this
particular case, they would have

00:14:09.920 --> 00:14:16.170
to tab 87 times,
which is not likely to be something

00:14:16.170 --> 00:14:18.030
that anyone is going
to be willing to do.

00:14:18.030 --> 00:14:26.020
So making sure that you
can pull up the menu

00:14:26.020 --> 00:14:29.070
that you have dropped
down is pretty important.

00:14:29.070 --> 00:14:31.040
Usually that's going
to be through control.

00:14:31.040 --> 00:14:36.010
Like on this site, there was
supposed to be this little plus icon

00:14:36.010 --> 00:14:42.010
to the right of the
menu, the main menu item,

00:14:42.010 --> 00:14:44.150
but that had been disabled
at some point by the site.

00:14:44.150 --> 00:14:45.970
And so it wasn't
working on BlackPast.

00:14:48.510 --> 00:14:50.460
Now I do have a caveat here.

00:14:50.460 --> 00:14:51.600
Why this is a problem.

00:14:51.600 --> 00:14:55.000
I say it probably exponentially
increases the amount of time needed

00:14:55.000 --> 00:15:01.030
to move through a menu, but it
would not increase that amount

00:15:01.030 --> 00:15:07.250
of time if you implement arrow key
navigation such that you can go down

00:15:07.250 --> 00:15:12.240
into the menu and then press
the right or the left arrow key

00:15:12.240 --> 00:15:16.400
to go to the next main menu item.

00:15:19.490 --> 00:15:23.270
You would not necessarily need
to have a distinct control

00:15:23.270 --> 00:15:25.830
to pull the menu back
up if you can do that.

00:15:25.830 --> 00:15:29.390
And we will talk about that
a little bit more later on,

00:15:29.390 --> 00:15:34.430
but problem two is problematic.

00:15:34.430 --> 00:15:42.430
Problem three,
if the items in your menu drop down

00:15:44.760 --> 00:15:48.600
do not have
aria-expanded attribute.

00:15:49.940 --> 00:15:53.860
Now, the aria-expanded
attribute is just something

00:15:53.860 --> 00:15:57.530
that helps assistive technology
users, primarily screen reader users.

00:15:57.530 --> 00:16:02.650
So when they move
their focus into the –

00:16:03.800 --> 00:16:07.170
in this case, for I'm looking
at Black Past site again -

00:16:07.170 --> 00:16:13.720
African American history main
menu item, they would hear,

00:16:13.720 --> 00:16:16.650
if it was in the collapse
state, if it was not expanded,

00:16:16.650 --> 00:16:21.420
they would hear African
American history link collapsed.

00:16:21.420 --> 00:16:25.510
And that would indicate to them,
oh, there's a sub menu here.

00:16:25.510 --> 00:16:32.720
So if I expand this menu,
the next place I go to is going

00:16:32.720 --> 00:16:33.720
to be inside the menu.

00:16:35.030 --> 00:16:37.610
Or if they come into
here and they hear

00:16:37.610 --> 00:16:39.975
African American
history link expanded,

00:16:39.976 --> 00:16:41.690
they are automatically going

00:16:41.690 --> 00:16:44.690
to think, OK,
so this is a drop down menu

00:16:44.690 --> 00:16:47.700
and I'm moving into it
with my next key press

00:16:49.070 --> 00:16:53.840
If they do not get that collapsed
or expanded notification,

00:16:53.840 --> 00:16:57.370
then they will add a new menu
item and end up thinking,

00:16:57.370 --> 00:17:00.090
Oh I'm here in African
American history.

00:17:00.090 --> 00:17:05.650
My next stop is going to
be the next main menu item.

00:17:05.650 --> 00:17:11.790
But after they get through six
or seven of these unrelated

00:17:11.790 --> 00:17:18.630
or non-high-level menu items,
they are going to start thinking

00:17:18.630 --> 00:17:26.630
or realizing that this may
not be what they think it is.

00:17:28.120 --> 00:17:31.180
But if they have that aria-expanded
attribute, it's going to work.

00:17:32.270 --> 00:17:33.160
Who else this affects?

00:17:33.160 --> 00:17:35.910
Refreshable Braille device users.

00:17:35.910 --> 00:17:39.540
So people who can not
see and can not hear.

00:17:42.220 --> 00:17:46.350
Why this is a problem once again,
they won't understand the menu

00:17:46.350 --> 00:17:47.190
and where they are in it.

00:17:47.190 --> 00:17:50.870
So they will have an erroneous
conception of what's going on

00:17:50.870 --> 00:17:55.410
and might get frustrated
after going through 20 things

00:17:55.410 --> 00:17:57.120
that they think are
primary menu items

00:17:57.120 --> 00:17:59.725
that are actually sub menu items.

00:18:03.740 --> 00:18:08.050
Or if your menu drops down on
click like this, for example.

00:18:08.050 --> 00:18:10.790
This African American history
would drop down as you click

00:18:10.790 --> 00:18:12.690
on the African
American history thing.

00:18:14.640 --> 00:18:19.710
The screen reader user may not
know what's happened at all.

00:18:19.710 --> 00:18:23.340
If you do not have an
expanded or contracted state,

00:18:24.360 --> 00:18:26.700
they would click on it
and it would drop down,

00:18:26.700 --> 00:18:28.126
but they would not
have any indication

00:18:28.127 --> 00:18:29.150
that anything has happened.

00:18:29.150 --> 00:18:32.090
They’d think maybe something
had just gone wrong and they are

00:18:32.090 --> 00:18:34.240
in no place now.

00:18:34.240 --> 00:18:35.290
So that could be problematic.

00:18:36.360 --> 00:18:42.280
All right, a kind of a sidebar,
the best practice for menus I've kind

00:18:42.280 --> 00:18:49.510
of decided or found is if you
have five to seven menu items,

00:18:49.510 --> 00:18:51.490
just put them in the main menu.

00:18:51.490 --> 00:18:54.390
Don't worry about
having dropdowns at all.

00:18:54.390 --> 00:18:59.940
And that's highly accessible
because then you don't have

00:18:59.940 --> 00:19:01.240
to worry about aria-expanded.

00:19:01.240 --> 00:19:03.870
You do not have to worry
about, does it drop down?

00:19:03.870 --> 00:19:04.870
Does it not?

00:19:05.690 --> 00:19:07.200
So that's super great.

00:19:07.200 --> 00:19:13.140
But if you have 15 to 20 or
more drop downs, you want them,

00:19:13.140 --> 00:19:16.530
or 15 or 20 or more items that
you want to fit into your menu,

00:19:16.530 --> 00:19:19.600
you definitely want drop downs.

00:19:19.600 --> 00:19:23.300
And you will need to make sure that
the aria-expanded attribute is there

00:19:23.300 --> 00:19:27.710
so that the drop down
works for people.

00:19:29.160 --> 00:19:29.900
OK.

00:19:29.900 --> 00:19:35.500
And here we go with our next
slide assessing the problems.

00:19:35.500 --> 00:19:36.500
So the next section.

00:19:38.620 --> 00:19:40.660
So how to assess.

00:19:40.660 --> 00:19:45.630
So if you are working on your
webpage or someone else's,

00:19:45.630 --> 00:19:50.670
and you want to see or
assess whether the menu

00:19:50.670 --> 00:19:57.650
that's in there is accessible,
well, use a keyboard.

00:19:57.650 --> 00:19:58.650
Start out that way.

00:19:59.490 --> 00:20:01.380
So you're going to hit tab.

00:20:01.380 --> 00:20:04.510
You're going to tab right
through the skip link

00:20:04.510 --> 00:20:07.230
that will probably pop
up first or second.

00:20:07.230 --> 00:20:10.560
Then you should be able to
tab into the actual menu.

00:20:10.560 --> 00:20:13.190
And you are just going to
start tabbing through it.

00:20:13.190 --> 00:20:17.760
If you get to a menu
item that is a drop-down,

00:20:20.020 --> 00:20:23.680
when you tab into it,
does it drop-down?

00:20:23.680 --> 00:20:26.090
If it doesn't, you got trouble.

00:20:26.090 --> 00:20:28.540
And you're going to have to
figure out how to fix that.

00:20:28.540 --> 00:20:30.460
We'll talk about how to
fix it in just a minute.

00:20:30.460 --> 00:20:33.350
You are going to see
if the menu drops down.

00:20:33.350 --> 00:20:37.730
You're going to see if there's
a way to make it pull up.

00:20:37.730 --> 00:20:40.230
Next, you want to assess
with the screen reader

00:20:40.230 --> 00:20:45.070
because you can use the
standard error navigation

00:20:45.070 --> 00:20:47.550
on the screen reader to go
forward through the menu

00:20:47.550 --> 00:20:51.890
and listen for your screen reader
to say, collapsed or expanded,

00:20:51.890 --> 00:20:56.170
which indicates to you
that it has the collapsed

00:20:56.170 --> 00:20:59.320
or the Aria expanded attribute
on it like it should.

00:21:01.890 --> 00:21:05.580
And finally,
you probably want to inspect.

00:21:05.580 --> 00:21:12.120
So use your browser inspector
to inspect an element.

00:21:12.120 --> 00:21:14.850
Let's take a closer look at this.

00:21:16.740 --> 00:21:21.620
OK, so if you were to
inspect, this is using Chrome,

00:21:21.620 --> 00:21:25.790
but Firefox and the other browsers
are usually pretty similar.

00:21:26.900 --> 00:21:31.590
So you'd put your pointer over
the item that makes it drop down.

00:21:31.590 --> 00:21:35.000
You would right click
and choose inspect,

00:21:35.000 --> 00:21:37.390
which would open up your
element inspector here.

00:21:37.390 --> 00:21:45.390
What you are looking for to make
sure that the menu is dropping down

00:21:45.720 --> 00:21:48.910
and that the aria-expanded
attribute is there.

00:21:48.910 --> 00:21:52.240
You are looking to see
here on this element

00:21:52.240 --> 00:21:54.270
if there is this
aria-expanded equals true.

00:21:55.780 --> 00:22:00.440
As you can see here,
it was not this way initially,

00:22:00.440 --> 00:22:03.290
but I did remediate BlackPast
so that it does have

00:22:03.290 --> 00:22:05.430
the aria-expanded equals true.

00:22:05.430 --> 00:22:08.380
And as you can see a little
farther down this next one,

00:22:08.380 --> 00:22:11.590
global African American
history, that menu item,

00:22:11.590 --> 00:22:16.560
which is also a dropdown,
has the aria-expanded equals false.

00:22:16.560 --> 00:22:24.560
You want to make sure that when the
global African history menu item

00:22:24.830 --> 00:22:27.010
drops down that these two swap.

00:22:27.010 --> 00:22:30.680
So that your first one would
say aria-expanded false

00:22:30.680 --> 00:22:32.860
and the second one would
say aria-expanded true.

00:22:32.860 --> 00:22:40.520
If that's working, you're
golden, at least in this aspect.

00:22:40.520 --> 00:22:43.660
So that's good.

00:22:43.660 --> 00:22:44.660
All right.

00:22:46.750 --> 00:22:54.750
In preparing for this talk,
I looked through 15 theme sites

00:22:56.450 --> 00:22:57.850
of WordPress themes.

00:22:57.850 --> 00:23:01.520
So I looked through,
I went to the popular themes

00:23:01.520 --> 00:23:06.650
and I tried to find sites that
were built with those themes

00:23:06.650 --> 00:23:13.130
and I assessed them to see if they
had any of these three problems

00:23:13.130 --> 00:23:14.470
and here's what I found.

00:23:14.470 --> 00:23:16.800
And then I also looked
at five other big ones,

00:23:16.800 --> 00:23:19.930
Google and very
much and a few more.

