00:23:39.980 --> 00:23:41.670
I first got some
screen reader users.

00:23:43.330 --> 00:23:45.590
And that's almost half of them.

00:23:45.590 --> 00:23:52.750
So that's a huge number of
sites that did not work great.

00:23:52.750 --> 00:24:00.750
Of the ones that did drop
down on focus, seven of those,

00:24:02.340 --> 00:24:06.280
so seven of 11,
had no way to pull the menu back up.

00:24:06.280 --> 00:24:07.870
So once again,
that's going to be a problem too.

00:24:09.120 --> 00:24:15.410
And then of these 20 websites, 15 of
them had no aria-expanded attribute.

00:24:18.360 --> 00:24:24.940
So poor for screen reader users.

00:24:24.940 --> 00:24:29.790
The good news is there were four
sites that worked perfectly.

00:24:29.790 --> 00:24:36.640
Google had very limited drop downs,
but the one that they had worked.

00:24:36.640 --> 00:24:37.660
Merriam-Webster.

00:24:38.670 --> 00:24:40.430
So those were kind of
the industry sites.

00:24:40.430 --> 00:24:43.560
I don't know if they're probably
most certainly not built

