00:26:34.110 --> 00:26:35.700
about this Walker_Nav_Menu.

00:26:38.260 --> 00:26:41.860
There are ways that you
can completely swap it out.

00:26:41.860 --> 00:26:49.400
I have not found code that you
could swap in for it or instructions

00:26:49.400 --> 00:26:53.930
on how to do it to make sure
that you are changing your menu

00:26:53.930 --> 00:26:56.366
to actually be one
that is accessible,

00:26:56.367 --> 00:26:59.240
but presumably there is a way
to do that.

00:27:01.880 --> 00:27:03.410
But let's look at
some other solutions

00:27:03.410 --> 00:27:07.930
that are probably more
likely helpful for you.

00:27:08.990 --> 00:27:14.650
So the solution for
drop-down only on hover.

00:27:14.650 --> 00:27:19.120
So if it only drops down when you
hover, usually you can fix this

00:27:19.120 --> 00:27:20.860
with just some CSS remediation.

00:27:22.600 --> 00:27:25.480
So adding something
to the stylesheet.

00:27:25.480 --> 00:27:29.310
So you're going to make sure that
the menu drops down on focus.

00:27:33.780 --> 00:27:41.780
So you'll inspect an element and
then you are going to look here

00:27:42.080 --> 00:27:44.750
in the style in this first
element state, you are going

00:27:44.750 --> 00:27:47.690
to click the hover and you are
going to figure out which one

00:27:47.690 --> 00:27:55.300
of these items is actually causing
the on-hover for it to drop down.

00:27:55.300 --> 00:27:58.180
And so by clicking
and unclicking hover

00:27:58.180 --> 00:28:01.470
with different items selected
here in the inspector,

00:28:03.650 --> 00:28:07.160
you will figure out which one of
those is triggering the drop-down.

00:28:07.160 --> 00:28:12.690
Then you can scroll down in
the rules here to figure out

00:28:12.690 --> 00:28:16.540
what's changing, figure out where in
the style sheet it is changing it.

00:28:16.540 --> 00:28:20.670
And then if you just add a
hover declaration to that,

00:28:20.670 --> 00:28:28.010
add a focus declaration to the hover
declaration that's already there.

00:28:31.320 --> 00:28:33.740
So let me see if I
got all my things.

00:28:33.740 --> 00:28:36.960
Use the browser dev tools,
add a focus declaration to it,

00:28:36.960 --> 00:28:39.430
and you should get it.

00:28:39.430 --> 00:28:40.910
OK, next.

00:28:42.010 --> 00:28:48.860
For the missing aria-expanded,
you are going to need

00:28:48.860 --> 00:28:51.410
to do some JavaScript remediation.

00:28:51.410 --> 00:28:56.590
So use JavaScript to modify
the proper aria-attributes,

00:28:56.590 --> 00:28:59.740
which does add some weight
to your site's load time.

00:28:59.740 --> 00:29:03.860
So anytime you add JavaScript,
that's one more resource,

00:29:03.860 --> 00:29:06.100
and it will take a
little bit longer.

00:29:06.100 --> 00:29:14.100
So that's a consideration, but if
it's adding this essential ability,

00:29:14.340 --> 00:29:17.660
it's definitely worth it.

00:29:17.660 --> 00:29:20.730
This only works if visitors have
JavaScript enabled in their browsers.

00:29:20.730 --> 00:29:24.620
And 1.2% of Internet users do
not have JavaScript enabled,

00:29:24.620 --> 00:29:29.470
which is actually a huge number
of visitors, 62 million a year,

00:29:31.680 --> 00:29:34.240
that do not have
JavaScript enabled.

00:29:34.240 --> 00:29:41.230
So it's just something you're going
to have to deal with or accept,

00:29:41.230 --> 00:29:45.570
that it's not going to work
for everyone, unfortunately.

00:29:45.570 --> 00:29:50.900
But how do you do it if you're
missing this aria-expanded attribute?

00:29:50.900 --> 00:29:53.480
Well,
you got to select the element.

00:29:53.480 --> 00:29:57.330
And I have on the right
side of the screen, an image

00:29:57.330 --> 00:30:04.630
of the BlackPast site with
the JavaScript console open.

00:30:04.630 --> 00:30:10.160
You can see some of the
things that I wrote here.

00:30:10.160 --> 00:30:13.780
You can try at first in
the JavaScript console.

00:30:16.270 --> 00:30:20.260
And then if it works there,
then you can add it to a resource,

00:30:20.260 --> 00:30:22.310
[Inaudible 30:27]

00:30:22.310 --> 00:30:25.540
JavaScript file that is
called throughout the site.

00:30:25.540 --> 00:30:33.010
But you got to select the element
and then use the set attribute method

00:30:33.010 --> 00:30:38.860
to set the aria-expanded to
false before it is dropping down

00:30:38.860 --> 00:30:42.100
and true when it does drop down.

00:30:42.100 --> 00:30:44.620
You are going to test,
test and test, in the console,

00:30:45.710 --> 00:30:48.330
in a dev environment,
in the live environment.

00:30:48.330 --> 00:30:51.850
Make sure that this works
the way that you expect it to

00:30:51.850 --> 00:30:53.570
or that you want it to.

00:30:53.570 --> 00:31:00.290
All right, so a little closer
look at what this looks like.

00:31:00.290 --> 00:31:05.990
So you can see the code that I used
here or that I tested in the console.

00:31:09.580 --> 00:31:12.770
But in addition to setting the
initial aria-expanded attribute

00:31:12.770 --> 00:31:16.610
of aria-expanded equals
false, you will also need

00:31:16.610 --> 00:31:22.340
to add an event listener on focus
that sets the aria-expanded attribute

00:31:22.340 --> 00:31:25.630
to true and another
one on the blur.

00:31:25.630 --> 00:31:29.390
So another event listener on
blur that sets it back to false.

00:31:29.390 --> 00:31:37.390
So making sure that the aria-expanded
attribute is modified dynamically

00:31:40.430 --> 00:31:43.830
on the fly as the
states of this change.

00:31:46.060 --> 00:31:52.580
You can do something like this,
drop down items, i.addEventListener

00:31:53.970 --> 00:31:59.040
on focus, and then use
your function that adds

00:31:59.040 --> 00:32:02.510
or takes away the proper attribute.

00:32:03.760 --> 00:32:08.570
So this is scratching the
surface, not going deeply into

00:32:08.570 --> 00:32:13.830
how to do the JavaScript, but
probably you already know that bit.

00:32:13.830 --> 00:32:17.610
All right, let's talk about this
enhancement that I mentioned earlier

00:32:18.800 --> 00:32:24.440
of the arrow key navigation.

00:32:29.640 --> 00:32:34.430
If you have menus that drop down...
I have got an image

00:32:34.430 --> 00:32:42.430
of the BlackPass site once again
because it has implemented this.

00:32:44.240 --> 00:32:49.710
You'll see that it's an image
of somebody in one of the menus,

00:32:49.710 --> 00:32:52.380
but there's a little message
up above the menu that says,

00:32:52.380 --> 00:32:54.230
use the arrow keys
to navigate the menu.

00:32:54.230 --> 00:32:57.000
To enter the page, use the right
arrow key from the last menu item,

00:32:57.000 --> 00:32:59.020
or press escape at any time.

00:32:59.020 --> 00:33:02.840
So what arrow key navigation
does is it allows visitors

00:33:02.840 --> 00:33:05.750
who tab into the menu to
move their focus around it

00:33:05.750 --> 00:33:10.190
with the arrow keys, which kind of
makes it so that you do not have

00:33:10.190 --> 00:33:18.090
to worry about having a way to
suck the menu back up necessarily,

00:33:18.090 --> 00:33:22.680
because you can always just go to
the right, go to the next menu over.

00:33:25.020 --> 00:33:26.250
How to do it?

00:33:26.250 --> 00:33:28.167
It's not a simple process,

00:33:28.168 --> 00:33:31.780
but basically you add
key press event listeners

00:33:31.780 --> 00:33:35.410
while the menu item has
focus, and you push the focus,

00:33:35.410 --> 00:33:41.830
depending upon the key presses of
the right and the left arrow key,

00:33:41.830 --> 00:33:43.840
you push the focus to
the desired element.

00:33:46.250 --> 00:33:51.370
So it does require JavaScript, with
all the caveats that that requires.

00:33:51.370 --> 00:33:55.130
It is, however,
helpful for keyboard navigators.

00:33:56.150 --> 00:34:02.940
It's not necessarily super
helpful for all other users,

00:34:02.940 --> 00:34:04.450
like screen reader users.

00:34:04.450 --> 00:34:10.320
There's a way to make it work,
but it's a little bit convoluted,

00:34:10.320 --> 00:34:12.800
and so it may not be helpful to
them, but it's not problematic

00:34:12.800 --> 00:34:13.940
to them either.

00:34:13.940 --> 00:34:19.200
So it does not block their
ability to at least go

00:34:19.200 --> 00:34:22.250
through all these menu
items if they want to.

00:34:22.250 --> 00:34:30.250
It just makes it easier for keyboard
navigators and not worse for others.

00:34:31.990 --> 00:34:33.000
OK.

00:34:33.000 --> 00:34:38.530
So the easy way to do this, I would
say is use the Crow's Nest plugin,

00:34:38.530 --> 00:34:45.130
which is available on the
WordPress plugin directory.

00:34:45.130 --> 00:34:48.650
And also I have a QR code here.

00:34:50.130 --> 00:34:56.520
It's a plugin that enables this
arrow key navigation on the menus.

00:34:56.520 --> 00:34:57.840
There are a few caveats.

00:34:57.840 --> 00:35:05.840
This plugin only works if the drop
down on focus is already enabled.

00:35:07.240 --> 00:35:09.130
So you have got to fix that first.

00:35:09.130 --> 00:35:17.130
And then you will set this plugin
up by targeting various elements,

00:35:25.220 --> 00:35:32.330
doing the CSS styles that
would target various elements.

00:35:33.993 --> 00:35:35.063
OK.

00:35:35.190 --> 00:35:37.210
So question.

00:35:38.540 --> 00:35:42.950
Remember that person on the lake that
we looked at the very first slide?

00:35:42.950 --> 00:35:50.480
Wouldn’t you rather have this
one paddling around your lake.

00:35:50.480 --> 00:35:57.380
Notice he's ready to stay, this
guy, he's got his fishing tackle,

00:35:57.380 --> 00:36:02.040
his fishing pole,
and he's got these oars.

00:36:02.040 --> 00:36:06.370
And so he is able to paddle around
the site, he's going to stay.

00:36:08.750 --> 00:36:12.820
That's what you want to
do with your navigation.

00:36:12.820 --> 00:36:15.420
Give your visitors
the proper paddles,

00:36:15.421 --> 00:36:24.110
the way to get around your site,
and they will stay longer.

00:36:24.110 --> 00:36:29.550
So you want to make sure that
your menu drops down on focus

00:36:29.550 --> 00:36:30.550
as well as hover.

00:36:31.240 --> 00:36:35.140
Do this by adding or adjusting
your CSS to add a focus trigger

00:36:35.140 --> 00:36:38.520
to your hover styles
that make that happen.

00:36:38.520 --> 00:36:41.380
Make sure that your menu has
a mechanism to suck back up,

00:36:42.940 --> 00:36:45.220
for keyboard and
screen reader users.

00:36:45.220 --> 00:36:48.780
So when it drops down,
you want it to have a way to come up

00:36:48.780 --> 00:36:52.220
or else they will be tapping
through the entire dropdown list,

00:36:52.220 --> 00:36:55.370
which is not great
if it's extensive.

00:36:56.810 --> 00:36:59.960
Or you can add arrow key
navigation as we have talked about.

00:37:01.460 --> 00:37:05.480
Make sure that your menu has
the proper aria attributes

00:37:05.480 --> 00:37:10.450
so it can be understood by
screen readers and their users.

00:37:12.850 --> 00:37:15.720
