00:47:19.293 --> 00:47:24.310
<v Deneb> So, that is actually
something I should have brought up

00:47:24.310 --> 00:47:25.070
in the presentation.

00:47:25.070 --> 00:47:29.370
You do need to make sure that
your menu works both in desktop

00:47:29.370 --> 00:47:36.550
and mobile for keyboard
navigators and screen readers

00:47:36.550 --> 00:47:38.800
because it is different.

00:47:38.800 --> 00:47:44.360
Typically, your mobile menu
would have a single dropdown.

00:47:44.360 --> 00:47:50.420
I mean, it's the hamburger
button that you click on,

00:47:50.420 --> 00:47:52.770
and that would drop the menu down.

00:47:52.770 --> 00:47:56.000
But you still do need
to make sure that it has

00:47:56.000 --> 00:48:03.350
the proper aria-expanded
attribute, and that it can work

00:48:03.350 --> 00:48:07.660
on keyboard focus, because
sometimes people are going to be,

00:48:07.660 --> 00:48:12.090
just have a really narrow
browser, and they may

00:48:12.090 --> 00:48:13.930
still be using their
keyboard to navigate.

00:48:13.930 --> 00:48:17.980
And so you do need to check
the mobile menu as well.

00:48:17.980 --> 00:48:21.490
So apply the same standards to make
sure that the mobile menu works

00:48:21.490 --> 00:48:22.610
as well.

